The paper presents an approach to SAT encoding of combinatorial problems, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and data structures (cs.DS). The use of Boolean functions and CNF encodings suggests a connection to logic (cs.LO) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the focus on constraint solving and tool development suggests a connection to software engineering (cs.SE).
